Lost to bajka dla dzieci z liceum gdzie zmienili zakończenie bo ludzie się kapowali do czego to prowadzi
The Wire to kawałek rzeczywistości, prawdziwe postacie i sytuację nie wysrywy w stylu CSI xd. I ten serial bardzo dobitnie mnie utwierdzil w tym że nie chciałbym mieszkać w USA. A w mieście gdzie biali są zdecydowaną mniejszością to już w ogóle. Nie mam tam kurwa akcji, pościgów ani zwrotów akcji z dupy, cliffhangerow tylko policyjne śledztwo które się ciągnie przez 5 sezonow, brud, korupcja, policyjne błędy itp. Przez 5 sezonów tylko jeden policjant z tego wydziału strzela z broni i zabija drugiego policjanta w wypadku. Poza tym jest wolno, spokojnie i obserwujesz upadek tych ludzi, albo rozwoj niektorych. A jak ktoś ginie to nie w strzelaninie gdzie zabija 10 typa i umiera jak bohater tylko dostaje kule kupując fajki w sklepie i tyle go było

posts.com:
Un giorno una cacata solitaria
abbandonata ai bordi di un sentiero,
complice Luglio e l’ olezzo dell’ aria,
s’ innamorò di “strunzo” di pompiere.

Era ella aggraziata e formosetta,
lui era grosso, scuro, prorompente.
Lei ricordava un piccolo cappello.
Lui torreggiava: imponente e bello.

E in una sera tutta profumata,
con la complicità d’ un gran moscone,
lui ricevette la dichiarazione
della piccola cacca innamorata.

Lui si commosse, essendo triste e solo
e da nessuno mai considerato.
Volle subito bene a “cacatella”,
di più che al culo che l’ avea creato.

Ma per sfortuna erano lontani.
E sol la luna, i sassi e le verzure
del piccolo viale solitario,
potevano conoscere i tormenti
di quei due timidissimi escrementi.

E un bel mattino, erano le otto,
un secchio d’ acqua, lesto, da un balcone,
l’ effetto provocò sul grande amore,
come il famoso libro galeotto,
che a Paolo ed a Francesca prese il core.

Benedicendo insieme la secchiata
in fine, al cor si strinsero gli amanti.
Piccoli oggetti, dell’ amore indegni,
scambiarono tra loro, come pegni.

E scivolando nell’ acqua delle alici,
seguiti dai “moschilli” planarono, felici.
Così finì che cacca di stiratrice
a nozze convolò con stronzo di pompiere
e dopo in viaggio stettero abbracciati
tra due cocci di “cantaro” spaccati.

posts.com:
>>176198426
>Easy
>>I just killed him
>Ich toetete *ihn.
fine in writing, but in conversation (like if this were a line in a movie) you usually use Perfekt:
Ich habe ihn (gerade) getötet.
>>Where is the dog
>Wo ist *der Hund?
it's Nominativ, i.e. 'der Hund' is the subject. 'den Hund' would be Akkusativ, i.e. a direct object most of the time.
if you reorder the sentence maybe it's easier to see:
Der Hund ist wo? Der Hund ist im Bad. [Nominativ]
Wohin hast du den Hund gebracht? / Wo hast du den Hund hingebracht? [Akkusativ]
>>The boat sailed to Fiji
>Das Boot ging *nach Fiji.
'gehen', 'fahren' or 'auslaufen' is ok too, but 'to sail' - 'segeln'. 'fahren' is probably the most common word to use here.
for cities and countries you use 'nach'. this way you could use 'zu':
Das Boot fuhr zu den Fiji-Inseln.
>>the boy ate fish
>Der Junge ass *Fisch/Fische.
countable vs. uncountable. 'Fisch' (uncountable) is more common. 'Fische' would be multiple fish, but they can be of the same kind.
>>The teacher was angry
>Die Lehrerin war *wuetend.
>>The little red ball
>Das kleines roten Ball.
Der kleine rote Ball.

posts.com:
>>176217563
Srpska reč mazda (nekad plata,

It's an old Polish word!

Indo-European *misdʰós > Proto Germanic *mizdō (note the Verner's Law change *s>*z) > Proto West Germanic *mizdu (shortening of unstressed final *ū to *u) > Old English 1 meord (the original *z often gets rhotacised to *r in Old English when preceding a coronal consonant, and if there is an *i preceeding it, said *i gets lowered and, in this case, broken by *r too into eo)/Old English 2 mēd (in some cases, the *z is often lost after that *i instead of becoming *r, but the *i still gets lowered and also lengthened to compensate for the loss of the consonant [I'm assuming due to the isochronous nature of Germanic languages], so we have dialectal variation meord/mēd) > Middle English meed (not sure what happened to the variant meord, but meed reflects mēd) > Modern English meed

In Slavic *misdʰós becomes *mьzdà (Polish/Serbian/Czech mzda, mazda [cf. also odmazda]) for reasons you probably already know.

posts.name: Anonymous

>>176240583
Yeah, so it seems like you've got three categories: back vowels, front rounded vowels, and front unrounded vowels. If a stem has one of those categories, then the suffix vowel is in the same category, but I'm not sure which vowel exactly in that category comes next. Like, if it's an a, then what category vowel is next? I'm not sure how regular that is.
But, there are also neutral vowels: e, é, i, í. If the stem has a neutral and a back vowel, then the suffix uses a back vowel. If the stem only has neutral vowels, then it takes a front vowel, rounded or unrounded depending on the category.
It's quite complex already, but it will probably just make more sense as I learn vocab and work at it.

Jan Sjunnesson åtalas för hets mot folkgrupp

Orsaken till åtalet är en kommentar på Twitter där Sjunnesson beskrev åldringsrån som "en romsk specialitet".

Det var djurplågaren Tomas Åberg, tidigare projektledare på Näthatsgranskaren, som polisanmälde inlägget som hets mot folkgrupp.

Tomas Åberg fick nyligen journalisten och debattören Joakim Lamotte dömd för grovt förtal efter att denne i inlägg på Facebook konstaterat att Åberg är en djurplågare. Han har också fått en rad pensionärer fällda för att ha delat Lamottes inlägg.

> Kriminellt även om det är sant

Jan Sjunnesson själv hävdar att han har läst om polisgruppen Circa, som specialiserar sig på att kartlägga åldringsbrott och dess förövare, och att han baserade sin kommentar på den informationen.

– I boken ”Romer i Sverige” av Karl-Olov Arnstberg säger dåvarande chefen för Circa-gruppen att det är en typ av brott som nästan alltid begås av romer, säger Sjunnesson till Bulletin.

Regionpolitikern Bertil Malmberg (SD) dömdes nyligen för hets mot folkgrupp efter att ha sagt att sydsudaneser har mycket låg IQ, trots att detta är sant och belagt i forskningen.

Näthatsgranskaren, som tidigare finansierades med statliga bidrag, har genom massanmälningar fått 350 personer åtalade för hets mot folkgrupp. Det rör sig ofta om pensionärer som i Facebook-inlägg uttryckt sin frustration över den svenska invandringspolitiken.

“When it comes to using deadly force to recover your stolen property, Texas juries will have a three-step process to decide if you were legally justified.

Step 1: The jury must find that you were justified under Texas Penal Code section 9.41 to use force to stop a trespasser or an interference with your property.
Step 2: The jury must decide whether you had a reasonable belief that deadly force was immediately necessary to prevent a perpetrator from fleeing immediately after committing a burglary, robbery, aggravated robbery, or theft during the nighttime.
Step 3: The jury must find that when you used deadly force to protect property, you reasonably believed it could not have been protected or recovered by other means; or using something less than deadly force would expose you to a substantial risk of death or serious bodily injury.
If the jury finds you were reasonable in your actions under all three of these steps, they should find your use of deadly force legally justified“
